The English Valleys Community School District is looking for a part-time School Nurse to start immediately. Applicants must hold a valid Iowa Board of Nursing RN License to practice nursing in Iowa.

post_text:
I've had a lot of people asking if we could use anything.

Here are a few items that we could use:

1) Bottled Water and/or New Refillable Water Bottles - Due to COVID-19 restrictions, our communal drinking fountains will be turned off.

We're asking all students to bring a reusable water bottle each day - and then take it home to be sanitized at night.

We'd like some cases of bottled water for students who forget to bring their water bottles back to school AND we'd also like some new refillable water bottles for students who may not have their own.

2) Travel Sized Tissues - To avoid spreading germs we would like some individual/travel tissue packets.

3) Clorox Wipes - We will be doing a lot of cleaning and the district is supplying cleaning supplies, but we would like to have wipes on hand if needed.

You can drop off any donations at the high school or email hlightfoot@english-valleys.k12.ia.us

Thanks for all that you do to support the school!
#bearstrong

Food Service Worker

The English Valleys Community School District is looking for an Anticipated Food Service Worker to work 5.5 hours/day. This position is a cook to aid in the preparation, serving, and cleaning up of meals as directed by the Food Service Director. Must be able to work independently, as well as with others. Ability to lift 40 pounds repetitively and be ServSafe certified or able Successfully complete the ServSafe certification

Wages will be discussed during the Interview. Food services or cooking experience is preferred.

To apply, please submit your application through http://teachiowa.gov/ and include: resume and references. You may also complete a paper application located on www.evbears.com, under District Info, click on employment opportunities. If you experience any problems submitting your application or have any questions, please feel free to contact the English Valleys CSD District Office at 319-664-3634.

shared_text:
Iowa Department of Human Services
July 11 at 5:46 PM ·

Watch your mail for this card!

Pandemic food assistance benefits cards are being mailed to 153,431 Iowa children the next two weeks. If your child was enrolled as a Pre-K through grade 12 student in either a public school or, non-public school that participates in the National School Lunch Program and received Free and Reduced Price School Meals as of March 16, 2020, you will receive this card in a white envelope with an Austin, TX return address.

For full program details, including how to activate the card and what it can be used for, please visit our website - https://dhs.iowa.gov/P-EBT

post_text:
The English Valleys Fitness Center will be open beginning June 1, 2020 per the Governor Reynolds's proclamation.

To stay consistent with the reopening of our school buildings the Competition Gym track will not be open for public use until July 1, 2020.

Please follow the Iowa Department of Public Health guidelines in regards to Covid-19 procedures as our facilities begin to open which includes but is not limited to: practicing social distancing, wearing masks when in close proximity to others, bring your own water, wash your hands often and stay home if you feel ill.

Also please remember to disinfect the equipment before and after each use.

If you have any additional questions please contact Heather Lightfoot at hlightfoot@english-valleys.k12.ia.us

These instructions are mailed with report cards as well:

PowerScheduler is now open! Students who will be in grades 9th - 12th next year, should use it to schedule their classes. Students who will be in grades 6th - 8th will be scheduled by Mrs. Horras. If you have any questions, please contact Ms. Horras at dhorras@english-valleys.k12.ia.us

Everything you need to schedule your classes can be found on our website, http://www.evbears.com/schedule-builder

TONIGHT, April 17th, the English Valleys Student Council will be sponsoring a “Light the Lights” event. The FOOTBALL, SOFTBALL and BASEBALL LIGHTS will be turned on at 8:00pm right after the victory bell is rung and remain on until 8:25pm when the victory bell is rung again. This will signify the twenty-five days that school has been closed, as of April 17th. The lights being a reminder to us that we are still united as students, staff, and community during this time.

If you would like to drive by the English Valleys High School during the event, we ask that you drive west toward the high school on Broad St, turn right onto Knoll Ridge and back to Washington Street. You are welcome to honk as you pass the victory bell.

Please do not leave your vehicle and remain off school grounds.

shared_text:
Jennifer De Boef Grove
April 23 at 8:29 AM ·

Dear Nolan Grove,

Congratulations! You have been named to the Des Moines Register’s Academic All-State team. Only 242 of Iowa’s roughly 40,000 high school seniors achieved this honor in 2020. That’s quite an accomplishment!

I’m writing to let you (and your parents) know the Academic All-State section will run Sunday (April 26) in the Des Moines Register print edition. The articles will roll out online Monday morning (April 27) at DesMoinesRegister.com.

Thank you, and once again, congratulations!

Charles Flesher
Community Content Editor

Des Moines Register

PART OF THE USA TODAY NETWORK

The baseball, softball, little league and football field lights will be turned on at 8:00 pm right after the victory bell is rung and remain on until 8:30 pm when the victory bell is rung again. If you would like to drive by the English Valleys High School during the event, we ask that you drive toward the high school west up Broad street, turn right onto Knoll Ridge and back to Washington Street. You are welcome to honk as you pass the victory bell!

PLEASE DO NOT LEAVE YOUR VEHICLE AND REMAIN OF SCHOOL GROUNDS! THANK YOU FOR SUPPORTING OUR ENGLISH VALLEYS FAMILY!

Sophomores and Juniors: The ACT is now showing IOWA VALLEY as a JUNE 13th test site. You may switch from your April 4th canceled date to June 13th at no charge by May 8th.

For sophomores that are unsure of whether or not they want to test in June, Iowa Valley will host again next April. However, it would be good to get a baseline score and then work to improve on the areas as needed.

If you have any questions, please contact Ms. Horras (dhorras@english-valleys.k12.ia.us).

post_text: On Friday, April 17th, the English Valleys Student Council will be sponsoring a “Light the Lights” event. The football field lights will be turned on at 8:00pm right after the victory bell is rung and remain on until 8:25pm when the victory bell is rung again. This time signifies the twenty-five days that school has been closed, as of April 17th. The lights being on reminds us that we are still united as students, staff, and community during this time. If you would like to drive by the English Valleys High School during the event, we ask that you drive toward the high school west up Broad street, turn right onto Knoll Ridge and back to Washington Street. You are welcome to honk as you pass the victory bell. Please do not leave your vehicle and remain off school grounds.

post_text:
Prom Announcement

Due to the Governor of Iowa extending the State Public Health Emergency Declaration until April 30th, which includes the closure of all schools until the end of April, we have made the difficult decision to cancel prom activities this year.

The Governor's proclamation includes closures of restaurants, previously identified retail stores, bans non-essential travel and forbids gatherings of more than 10 people.

Our hearts are certainly with our families and students whose lives have been disrupted. We must work together, now more than ever, to protect the health of our community and decrease the spread of the Coronavirus.

Hello everyone! A reminder that the North English Public Library has online resources available. (You will have to download a free app for this.) There are two ways to access our eBooks. Go to www.northenglish.lib.ia.us and click on the Bridges icon. It will ask for our login, which is the zip-code of North English (52316) PLUS your library card number. So it is a long number. If you do not know your library card number you can email me at ashannahan@northenglish.lib.ia.us and I will send it to you. The other way is to go to http://bridges.lib.overdrive.com and choose North English Public Library and then login the same way. They are currently trying to make more titles available during these difficult times, so check back if you do not find anything you like right away. As a side note-I will only be checking my mail a couple times a day, so I may not get back to you immediately.
